a, b = map(int, input().split())
minN = 0
maxN = 0
maxK = 0
for i in range(a, b + 1):
    b = str(bin(i))[-1]
    o = str(oct(i))[-1]
    h = str(hex(i))[-1]
    n = ""
    if h in "abcdif":
        n += h
        n += max(b, o)
        n += min(b, o)
    else:
        g = sorted([b, h, o], reverse=True)
        for j in g:
            n += j
    n = int(n, 16)
    if n > maxN:
        maxN = n
        minN = i
        maxK = 1
    elif n == maxN:
        maxK += 1
print(minN, maxK)
